ome.smuggler.core.msg

Interface MessageSink<M,D>

  • All Superinterfaces:
    ChannelSink<ChannelMessage<M,D>>
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    CountedScheduleSink, ReschedulingSink

    public interface MessageSink<M,D>
extends ChannelSink<ChannelMessage<M,D>>
    Encapsulates the consumption of an asynchronous message received from a channel. Messages have data to consume and possibly associated metadata.
    See Also:
    ChannelMessage, MessageSource

      • asDataSink

        default ChannelSink<D> asDataSink()
        Builds a channel sink that uses this message sink to consume data items D. The messages forwarded to the underlying consumer will all have empty metadata as any received metadata is discarded.
        Returns:
        a channel sink adapter.
